Durban - Robbers held up a domestic worker at her employers home in uMhlanga on Thursday. The robbery occurred at 11 am on Sylvan Grove in Umhlanga Rocks, north of Durban. Marshall Security spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said the five men derailed a driveway gate before storming the home. He said a domestic worker who was present at the time was confronted and held up at gunpoint while the men ransacked the home. "They took various items of electronic equipment. They fled in an awaiting getaway vehicle. Although seriously traumatized in the ordeal, the domestic worker did not suffer any physical injury. The suspects remain at large," Reenen said. Durban North police are investigating the robbery. In Westville four robbers entered a home in Queen Elizabeth Road on Wednesday. Colonel Thembeka Mbele, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said they robbed the homeowner of household items and other valuables at gunpoint. "They then fled the scene in a complainantâ€™s VW Polo. No injuries were sustained. A case of robbery has been opened at Westville police station for investigation," Mbele said. Daily News